I found a solution to my problem in another question (so my question will be counted as repeated).

The solution (to my problem) can be found [here][1]. What I needed was a `MediatorLiveData` to combine my two live data into one live data and observe it.

Credit goes to [@EpicPandaForce][2]

```java
    public class CombinedLiveData2&lt;A, B&gt; extends MediatorLiveData&lt;Pair&lt;A, B&gt;&gt; {
    private A a;
    private B b;

    public CombinedLiveData2(LiveData&lt;A&gt; ld1, LiveData&lt;B&gt; ld2) {
        setValue(Pair.create(a, b));

        addSource(ld1, (a) -&gt; { 
             if(a != null) {
                this.a = a;
             } 
             setValue(Pair.create(a, b)); 
        });

        addSource(ld2, (b) -&gt; { 
            if(b != null) {
                this.b = b;
            } 
            setValue(Pair.create(a, b));
        });
    }
}
```


