The `.*?` is a reluctant match so it won&#39;t gobble up everything.  The `?:` forces a non-capturing group so the inner group is group 1.  Matching multiples in a greedy fashion causes it to match across the entire string until all matches are exhausted leaving group 1 with the value of your last match.

