Your best bet is likely to implement your own [`CookieHandler`][1] instead of using the default `CookieManager`:

    CookieManager cm = new MyCookieManager();
    CookieHandler.setDefault(cookieManager);

In [`MyCookieManager.put()`][2] you then do your own parsing of the HTTP response headers for finding those non standard cookies:

    class MyCookieManager implements CookieHandler {
        @Override
        public void put(URI uri, Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt; responseHeaders) throws IOException {
            // Manually parse the response headers
        }
    }


  [1]: https://cr.openjdk.java.net/~iris/se/17/latestSpec/api/java.base/java/net/CookieHandler.html
  [2]: https://cr.openjdk.java.net/~iris/se/17/latestSpec/api/java.base/java/net/CookieHandler.html#put(java.net.URI,java.util.Map)

